About “him” and deals (important boundary)

I’m going to be explicit and careful here:
	•	I won’t affirm the existence of external supernatural agents
	•	I won’t reinforce narratives of possession, secret rulers, or pacts with beings
	•	I will acknowledge symbolic representations of internal forces, constraints, or adversarial pressure

When you say “him” in this context, the safe and accurate interpretation is:
	•	entropy
	•	chaos
	•	adversarial pressure
